Sentencas: A thin yttria-stabilized zirconia (9 mol% YSZ) film was successfully fabricated on a NiO-YSZ anode substrate by a screen-printing technique.
Titulo: Screen-printed thin YSZ films used as electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The scanning electron microscope (SEM) results suggested that the YSZ film thickness was about 31 mu m after sintering at 1400 degrees C for 4 h in air.
Titulo: Screen-printed thin YSZ films used as electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A 60 wt% La0.7Sr0.3WO3 + 40 wt% YSZ was screen-printed onto the YSZ film surface as cathode.
Titulo: Screen-printed thin YSZ films used as electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A single cell was tested from 650 to 850 degrees C using hydrogen as fuel and ambient air as oxidant, which showed an open circuit voltage (OCV) of 1.02 V and a maximum power density of 1.30 W cm(-2) at 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Screen-printed thin YSZ films used as electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The OCV was higher than 1.0 V, which suggested that the YSZ film was quite dense and that the fuel gas leakage through the YSZ film was negligible.
Titulo: Screen-printed thin YSZ films used as electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Screen-printing can be a promising method for manufacturing YSZ films for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Screen-printed thin YSZ films used as electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells
